          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The first   complete   measurements    of    angular",
                " distributions of          two-body          deuteron",
                " photodisintegration  differential  cross  section at",
                " photon energies above 1.6 GeV were performed at  the",
                " Thomas Jefferson National Accelerator Facility.  The",
                " results show a persistent forward-backward asymmetry",
                " up  to Egamma = 2.4 GeV, the highest-energy measured",
                " in this   experiment.   The   Hard   Rescattering",
                " and Quark-Gluon string models are in fair agreement",
                " with the results."
              ]
            }
          ],
